{
  "texts": [
    "It then follows, in the exact same way as for the prescribed Gauss curvature equation, that such a minimiser exists and, moreover, is a weak solution of (20b); see [Tay11, Ch. 14 §2].",
    "Elliptic regularity then shows that the weak solution is a classical solution and is smooth.",
    "Conformally related metrics on surfaces have the same Ricci curvature if and only if (the logarithm of) their conformal factor is harmonic; since B 2 is compact, any harmonic function is constant.",
    "This constant must be 1 by (20b), so the solution is unique.",
    "□We finish this section by recalling one approach to finding weakly conformal harmonic maps due to Schoen-Yau [SY79] and Sacks-Uhlenbeck [SU82]."
  ]
}